    Description Of The Program (In My Own Words):This program takes the size of an array from the user, reads the array elements, and prints all the elements using a for loop.
    Expected Input And Expected Outputs:
        Case 1:
              Expected Input: size=5 
              1
              2
              3
              4
              5

              Expected Output:1 2 3 4 5 
        Case 2:
              Expected Input: size=2
              1
              2
              

              Expected Output:1 2 
        Case 3:
              Expected Input:3
              6
              7
              8
              

              Expected Output:6 7 8
    Conclusion:The program successfully demonstrates how to input and display array elements using loops in C.
*/

#include<stdio.h>
int main()
{
int size;
printf("enter the size of the array : ");
scanf("%d",&size);


int array[size];
int index;


for (index=0;index<size;index++)
scanf("%d",&array[index]);


for(index=0;index<size;index++)
printf("%d",array[index]);
}
  